    "Dictionary methods differentiate based on word frequency and are often referred to as bag-of-words approaches.",
    "Figure 20 illustrates the process that algorithms following the dictionary model take to create a classifier.",
    "This process can be summarized as:",
    "Extracting subseries, or windows, from a time series; 2.",
    "Transforming each window of real values into a discrete-valued word (a sequence of symbols over a fixed alphabet); 3."
  ]
}